This paper presents a calculus for process interaction based on copyless message passing, which is a topic that falls under the area of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the type system used in the calculus, which is relevant to the area of distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper mentions Singularity OS, which is an operating system, placing the paper in the area of operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also discusses the prevention of faults and communication errors, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses a condition on endpoint types that prevents memory leaks, which is a topic related to logic in computer science (cs.LO).
